The remains of 14-year-old Keren Akpagher, who was a pupil at the Premier Academy Lugbe, in the Federal Capital Territory, Abuja, have been laid to rest amidst tears. The SS1 student of the school located in Lugbe died after she was allegedly raped by an unknown person, with a condom left in her private part. The pupil was laid to rest at her country home in Gboko Local Government Area of Benue State, North-Central Nigeria, on Sunday.